1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,152
You need someone to help with
the exercise, stand by with a towel...

2
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:05,918
...run errands.

3
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:10,875
Who cared about me yesterday? Nobody.
I think I'm gonna train myself, you know?

4
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,710
Without such good people around to help,
you don't have such a good chance.

5
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:18,638
Einstein flunked outta school. Twice.

6
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:20,955
- That so?
- Yeah.

7
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:26,359
Beethoven was deaf, Helen Keller was
blind. I think Rocky's got a good chance.

8
00:00:32,120 --> 00:00:35,635
- Want me to get you a beer, Paulie?
- You lookin' to do a good deed?

9
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:38,479
Keep outta my freakin' life!

10
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,796
- What did I do?
- Nothin'.

11
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:43,639
- Did I say something?
- You didn't say nothin'.

12
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:47,833
That's right, you didn't say nothin'!
Nothin' at all!

13
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:51,356
I gotta go.

14
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:54,275
Where's the freakin' pretzels?

15
00:00:57,160 --> 00:01:00,709
Goddamn the pretzels!
Hey, we don't have any beer!

16
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:05,196
I thought you were supposed
to pick up some beer!

17
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:15,716
How'd you like hearin'
your name on TV tonight?

18
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:19,354
I was shocked. Why'd you do that?

19
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:23,189
- Come on, you're puttin' me on, right?
- Absolutely.

20
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:26,949
- What time should I expect you?
- Oh, about seven.

21
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:29,036
Hey.

22
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:43,916
Hey.

23
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:48,350
You know I said that stuff on TV
didn't bother me none?

24
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,436
Yeah?

25
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:54,036
It did.

26
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:06,796
Listen, the reason I've
brought you here is because...

27
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,229
Have you got money
for trainin' expenses?

28
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:13,148
- I got a few dollars, you know?
- Well, here. Put this in your glove.

29
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:16,636
- What's this?
- 500 bucks. Don't worry about it.

30
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:21,633
You ain't never had any luck, but this time
Lady Luck may be in your corner.

31
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:24,638
- What do ya think?
- Maybe. Maybe...

32
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:29,834
- Hey, thanks for the money, Tony.
- It's OK. Don't worry about it. See ya.

33
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,359
- Wait a minute.
- What?

34
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:34,233
- You're in trainin'. Huh? Come on.
- Hey.

35
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,756
- Yo, Tony?
- What?

36
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,871
You gonna show up at the fight?

37
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,116
- Ringside.
- Hey, hey!

38
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,676
I'll see ya.

39
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,636
<i>(Rocky) Yeah!</i>

40
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:34,596
Hello, kid. I seen your light.
Can I come in?

41
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,790
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah. Good!

42
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:39,559
Hey, this is a nice place here.

43
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:42,717
Anyway, what I come to tell you
is that, uh...

44
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:46,997
...that what happened to you is freak luck.

45
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:50,157
- Yeah, freak luck.
- Ain't it true? Look at the other guys.

46
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:53,955
They're good fighters.
They're colourful, they got good records.

47
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:56,310
They fight their guts out for peanuts.

48
00:03:56,440 --> 00:04:00,353
But you... you got a shot at the title.

49
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:03,870
- Freak luck is a strange thing.
- Yeah, sure it is. Can I sit down?

50
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,309
Yeah, sure.

51
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:09,796
- What the hell are those?
- Oh, they're domestic turtles.

52
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:13,390
The one on top is Cuff and
the other is Link. The rest are marbles.

53
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,830
Yeah? They make good soup, do they?

54
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:20,396
Anyway, look, I'm here to warn ya...

55
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:24,798
...that you gotta be very careful
about this shot that you got at the title.

56
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:29,755
Because, I don't know, like the Bible says,
you ain't gonna get a second chance.

57
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:33,831
- Yeah, all right.
- You thought of that, huh?

58
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:36,997
Well, what you need is a manager.

59
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,956
A manager. Listen to me.

60
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:43,516
I know, because I've been
in this racket for 50 years.

61
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:46,757
- 50 years, huh?
- 50 years. God, I've seen it all.

62
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:49,519
All of it. You know what I done?

63
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:52,074
- What?
- I have done it all.

64
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:55,749
You shoulda seen me when
I knocked Giny Russel outta the ring.

65
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:59,759
Outta the goddamn ring, I tell ya.
September 14, 1923.

66
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:03,759
And it was the same night that
Firpo knocks Dempsey outta the ring.

67
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:06,792
- The same night. Who gets the publicity?
- Dempsey.

68
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:09,115
- That's right, but why?
- Cos he was champ.

69
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:12,232
No! Because he had a manager.

70
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:14,874
I had nothin', man.

71
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:18,436
I wanna show you somethin'.
Look at my face for a minute. Look.

72
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:23,270
I got 21 stitches over this left eye.
I got 34 stitches over this eye.

73
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:26,756
You know what?
I had my nose busted 17 times.

74
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:30,873
The last time was with
that fight with Sailor Mike.

75
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,878
I got the clippin' here. A good fight.

76
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,831
Read that.

77
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,916
Well, it doesn't matter.

78
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:41,112
Anyway, he put this vegetation on my ear.

79
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:45,392
Ah, Rocky Marciano!

80
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:50,433
You know, you kinda remind me
of the Rock, do you know that?

81
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:54,030
- You really think so?
- That's right. You move like him.

82
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:56,116
And you got heart, like he did.

83
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:59,357
Yeah, I got heart,
but I ain't got no locker, do I, Mick?

84
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:05,514
Uh... anyway, you know...

85
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:08,518
...when I begun in this business, kid...

86
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:14,156
Look, I wanna make a suggestion.
Don't drink that piss before a fight.

87
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:17,875
It's no good for ya.
You don't mind my sayin'...?

88
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:22,437
Anyway, when I started this racket,
pugs like us, we was treated like dogs.

89
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:28,032
For $10, you gotta tear somebody's throat
out. But I never had no management.

90
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:33,236
One time, this son of a bitch
that I fought, he put a nail right there.

91
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,430
- In his thumb?
- Yeah, in the glove.

92
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,915
And he punched
so many holes in my face...

93
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:42,955
...I had this spit shootin' outta my cheeks.
Can you imagine that?

94
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:46,436
When I tell you what I looked like
when I was in my prime...

95
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:49,313
I want ya to look at somethin'.
Will ya look at that?

96
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:53,433
That's the way I looked
before these guys got at me.

97
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,950
That's nice.
You don't take care of the picture, though.

98
00:06:57,080 --> 00:07:00,993
Well, I never had no management.
That was the trouble.

99
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:05,511
Now I got all this knowledge.
I got it up here and I wanna give it to you.

100
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:10,031
I wanna take care of you. I wanna make
sure all this shit that happened to me...

101
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:13,675
...doesn't happen to you.
You know what I mean?

102
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:17,429
- The fight's set.
- Listen to me. I wanna be your manager.

103
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:21,109
- You follow that, do you?
- The fight's set. I don't need no manager.

104
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:25,631
But you can't buy what I'm gonna give ya.
I've got pain and I've got experience.

105
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:28,797
I got pain and I got experience too.

106
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:32,435
- Now listen, kid...
- Hey, yo. Hey, Mick.

107
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:36,439
I needed your help about ten years ago.
You never helped me none.

108
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:39,632
- You didn't care.
- Well, if you wanted help...

109
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:43,639
I say, if you wanted help,
why didn't you just ask me, kid?

110
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:47,116
Look, I asked,
but you never heard nothin'!

111
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,196
Well, I...

112
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,956
I, uh...

113
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:55,115
I'm 76 years old.

114
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:01,116
And, uh...

115
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:24,516
Ah, shit.

116
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:37,433
Took you long enough to get here.

117
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:42,236
Ten years to come to my house. What's
the matter? You don't like my house?

118
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,590
My house stink?

119
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,950
That's right. It stinks!

120
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,389
I didn't ask no favours from you!

121
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,511
Don't throw it around!

122
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:55,873
<i>Talkin' about your prime.
What about my prime, Mick?</i>

123
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,635
At least you had a prime!

124
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:03,709
I ain't had no prime! I ain't had nothin'!
Legs are goin', everything's goin'!

125
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:08,834
Guy offers me a fight. Big deal! Wanna
fight the fight? Yeah, I'll fight the big fight.

126
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:12,350
I'm gonna go and fight that big fight.
I'm gonna get that!

127
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:15,119
I'm gonna get that!

128
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:17,993
And you wanna be ringside and see it?
Do ya?

129
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:22,033
You wanna help me out? Huh? Do you
wanna see me get my face kicked in?

130
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:26,836
Legs ain't workin', nothing's workin'!
They go "Go on, fight the champ!"

131
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,916
Yeah, I'll fight him.

132
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:33,719
Get my face kicked in.

133
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:38,789
You come around here! You wanna move
in with me? Come on in! It's a nice house!

134
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:41,878
Real nice! Come on in and move! It stinks!

135
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,995
This whole place stinks!

136
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:48,637
You wanna help me out?
Well, help me out!

137
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,638
Come on! Help me out! I'm standin' here!

138
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,797
<i>(alarm rings)</i>

139
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:53,837
<i>(radio) It's 28 degrees. We'll check that
forecast in a minute. I feel very... weird.</i>

140
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:57,475
<i>Very... Well,
the thing is I got vinyl seats in my car.</i>

141
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,512
<i>When I hit the seats this morning,
I just went "Whoo!"</i>

142
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:04,519
<i>I figured if I'm up, everybody
in the Delaware Valley should be up.</i>

143
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:08,315
<i>Do you agree? At three minutes
past four, what else are you gonna do?</i>

144
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:11,989
<i>- (ringing tone)
- (woman) Hello?</i>

145
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:15,715
<i>Good morning, Mrs Kramer!
This is Don Cabot, WYBG Philadelphia.</i>

146
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,638
<i>- How are you this morning?
- Huh? What?</i>

147
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:23,914
<i>I think you have a lot of nerve callin' me
at this hour in the morning! Goodbye!</i>

148
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:28,192
<i># WYBG</i>

149
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:34,432
<i># Philadelphia</i>

150
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:38,199
<i>Ha! We got Mrs Kramer up
and it's a good morning.</i>

151
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:42,359
<i>Boy, I need somethin' to struggle with.
28° - it's cold out there.</i>

152
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:47,554
<i>We've been getting away with murder
for weeks. Our high today could be 30.</i>

153
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:51,229
<i>Tonight we're back down in the 20° range,
colder in the suburbs.</i>

154
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:55,069
<i>And tomorrow, with a little bit of luck,
we may hit 40 somewhere.</i>

155
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:59,671
<i>But it's awfully chilly. Make sure you
have it bundled up before you bring it out.</i>

156
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:20,392
Come on. It stinks... Hey, come on!
It stinks in here, you know?

157
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:22,476
Yeah, I know.

158
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:26,839
Hey, do you kill all these things?

159
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:29,315
No, across the street.

160
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,553
This place looks like an animal morgue,
you know?

161
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:36,638
- It's a little cold in here, ain't it?
- Yeah.

162
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,435
Who killed all these things?

163
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:46,950
- What, are you crazy?
- Pay Gazzo or you end up on a hook.

164
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:49,389
Hey, Gazzo's a good man. You know that.

165
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:54,958
Hey, don't get excited. I know that. That's
why I want you to talk to him about me.

166
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:57,469
I can get me out of this stinkin' freezer.

167
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:02,879
Why don't you do yourself a favour?
Keep this job, because you eat better.

168
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,753
Moo... Does it ever snow in here?

169
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:11,199
Uh, you and my sister.
How are you gettin' along together?

170
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,116
How you think?

171
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:17,073
Uh, I'm not sure, Rock. What's the story?

172
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:21,599
- About what?
- What's the story? What's happening?

173
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:24,678
- You really like her?
- Sure I like her.

174
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:30,350
I don't see it. What's the attraction?

175
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:33,790
I don't know. It fills gaps, I guess.

176
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:37,913
- What's "gaps"?
- I don't know. She's got gaps, I got gaps.

177
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,634
Together we fill gaps. I don't know...

178
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:43,990
You ballin' her?

179
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:45,473
Hey!

180
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:48,558
Hey, you don't talk dirty about your sister.

181
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:52,315
You screwin' my sister?

182
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:57,670
You see? That's why I can't
connect you with Gazzo, Paulie.

183
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:01,839
Because you got a big mouth, you know?
You just talk too much.

184
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:06,033
<i>- It's gettin' cold in here. I'm goin' home.
- Cold in here?! It is cold in here!</i>

185
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:09,357
It stinks in here! And you stink!

186
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:35,910
<i>(cracking)</i>

187
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:38,600
You're breakin' the ribs.

188
00:16:56,640 --> 00:17:00,792
If you do that to Apollo Creed,
they'll put us in jail for murder.

189
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:05,000
I'll see you tomorrow mornin', OK?

190
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,514
- I turned the heat up.
- Thanks.

191
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:24,395
You know, your brother's a good man,
but he's awful pushy, you know?

192
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:37,636
- You want me to rub you down?
- No, I'm just sore, OK? I'll just sit here.

193
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:40,115
- You sure?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

194
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:46,238
Hey, come on. No foolin' around, all right?

195
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:48,237
I'm tired.

196
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:50,316
Hey, Adrian, I'm serious now.

197
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:54,319
There's no foolin' around durin' trainin'.
I wanna stay strong.

198
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:57,398
- You're not kiddin'.
- No, I ain't kiddin'.

199
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,871
- You sure?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

200
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,594
Why don't you just make the meat, OK?

201
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,550
OK, I'll make the meat.

202
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,156
Yo.

203
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:36,348
- It's OK.
- I'm sorry.

204
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,436
Hey.

205
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,356
Hey, c'mon.

206
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:45,196
C'mon.

207
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,910
Underneath. Underneath.

208
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,759
Underneath! Underneath! Come on!

209
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:12,348
Rock, hold it, hold it.
Hold it, Rock, will ya?

210
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:16,029
You're drivin' me crazy,
you're so sloppy. You're off balance.

211
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:20,950
Let's try this. Take this string. Tie it
to both ankles. Leave two feet of slack.

212
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:24,709
- I ain't never had good footwork.
- Never mind. You're off balance.

213
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:29,755
Marciano... He had the same problem
and this string cured it.

214
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:34,112
The idea is that if you can move
and hit without breakin' the string...

215
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:37,949
...you got balance. You become
a dangerous person. You follow?

216
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:40,514
- You're lookin' good, Rock.
- Thanks.

217
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:42,358
That's it. Underneath!

218
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:44,869
Hey, Rock, how about an autograph?

219
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:49,152
Get outta here! Don't you ever interrupt
me while I'm conductin' business.

220
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,874
Move your little chicken asses out.

221
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:55,788
Listen, kid. You...
You lay off that pet-shop dame.

222
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:58,229
Women weaken legs.

223
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:03,632
- Yeah, but I really like this girl...
