00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:19,153
In foreign countries during World War I
there was a picture of Uncle Sam...

446
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:21,111
...with his finger pointed -

447
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:25,518
...a recruiting poster for our fellows
in the army and the navy. "I want you!"

448
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:27,596
<i>(Stu) That's what he's doing a take on.</i>

449
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:30,518
- That's it. "Creed" he's yelling.
- "Creed in three."

450
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:32,915
What do you think that outfit cost?

451
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:35,190
<i>(fanfare)</i>

452
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:40,310
<i>(bell)</i>

453
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:45,633
Ladies and gentlemen...

454
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:49,389
...good evening. A very happy new year.

455
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:51,476
Welcome to Philadelphia.

456
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:54,558
<i>(Stu) Everybody who's anybody
is here tonight.</i>

457
00:42:56,200 --> 00:43:02,673
Time does not permit me to introduce
the many luminaries of politics...

458
00:43:02,800 --> 00:43:06,952
...show business and the sporting world
who are with us tonight.

459
00:43:07,560 --> 00:43:12,429
But I would like to present
one of the immortals of pugilism...

460
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:15,950
...a champion in and out of the ring.

461
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:18,640
Philadelphia's own Smokin' Joe...

462
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:21,752
...the beloved Mr Joe Frazier!

463
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:24,440
<i>(cheering, whistling and applause)</i>

464
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:35,109
Hi, how are you doing?
Don't hurt him, OK?

465
00:43:35,240 --> 00:43:38,357
<i>(Stu) What a credit he's been
in his career as a fighter.</i>

466
00:43:38,480 --> 00:43:40,596
He's coming over to talk with the champ.

467
00:43:40,720 --> 00:43:43,632
- Hey, Joe!
- You been dumpin' me long time.

468
00:43:43,760 --> 00:43:46,513
You next, Joe! You next, Joe!

469
00:43:47,600 --> 00:43:49,909
They must be friends.

470
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:58,992
Joe Frazier!

471
00:43:59,120 --> 00:44:03,591
Fight fans around the world, get settled
down, because it won't be long now.

472
00:44:03,720 --> 00:44:05,039
<i>(bell)</i>

473
00:44:05,160 --> 00:44:08,869
And now... for the main event!

474
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:14,914
On my left, the challenger.

475
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:20,118
In white trunks, weighing 190lb...

476
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:22,993
...Philadelphia's favourite son...

477
00:44:23,120 --> 00:44:27,636
...the Italian Stallion, Rocky Balboa!

478
00:44:27,760 --> 00:44:30,320
<i>(cheering and some booing)</i>

479
00:44:34,120 --> 00:44:38,636
And on my right,
wearing red, white and blue...

480
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:41,797
...weighing 210lb...

481
00:44:42,120 --> 00:44:45,192
...undefeated in 46 fights...

482
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:48,114
...the Master of Disaster...

483
00:44:48,240 --> 00:44:51,676
...the undisputed
heavyweight champion of the world...

484
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:55,669
<i>...Apollo Creed!
- (cheering)</i>

485
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:58,189
I want you! I want you!

486
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:02,995
You, chump! I want you!

487
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:05,395
You've both fought in Philadelphia before.

488
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:09,274
You know the rules. No low blows.
Watch your heads. No buttin'.

489
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:14,349
- Shake hands now and come out fightin'.
- Put your hands up, chump. Come on!

490
00:45:14,480 --> 00:45:18,758
<i>(Bill) A little body play goin' on there.
Rocky taking it carefully, though.</i>

491
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:22,509
He's just going over and being calm,
it looks like from here.

492
00:45:22,640 --> 00:45:25,074
There goes the big hat.

493
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:31,473
<i>(Stu) I've never seen a fighter
that concerned about his hair!</i>

494
00:45:39,160 --> 00:45:42,197
And there's the bell for round one.

495
00:45:42,320 --> 00:45:46,518
The fighters come out into the centre
of the ring, looking at each other.

496
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:51,395
Creed the champion zipping those
left-handed jabs, right in the head.

497
00:45:53,520 --> 00:45:56,671
The champ stinging
the slower challenger jabs at will.

498
00:45:56,800 --> 00:46:00,634
In fact, it looks like Rocky is
blocking the blows with his face.

499
00:46:00,760 --> 00:46:04,992
The champion doesn't look the best
he's ever been, but he's moving smoothly.

500
00:46:05,120 --> 00:46:08,908
Well, the champion is smiling now.
He's toying with his man.

501
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:13,556
Tryin' to give the fans their money's
worth. He's makin' a show of it.

502
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:17,036
And a very badly outclassed
challenger right now.

503
00:46:19,200 --> 00:46:21,270
<i>(Bill) Creed trying to
make this man make...</i>

504
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:24,198
See? Make him miss like that.

505
00:46:24,320 --> 00:46:26,959
<i>(Stu) Oh, the champ
is just taunting him now.</i>

506
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:32,235
Creed dancing around.

507
00:46:33,160 --> 00:46:35,549
I don't believe it! The champ is down!

508
00:46:35,680 --> 00:46:37,636
<i>(Bill) Yes, he is!</i>

509
00:46:42,720 --> 00:46:45,757
Creed is down! What a surprise this is!

510
00:46:47,040 --> 00:46:51,158
<i>(Stu) This is the first time the champion
has ever been knocked down.</i>

511
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:54,869
Six! Seven! Eight!

512
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:58,037
He appears to be all right.
Glancin' around...

513
00:46:58,400 --> 00:47:02,632
<i>(Mickey) Come on, Rock! Go to the ribs!
Let's go to work right now, Rock!</i>

514
00:47:04,120 --> 00:47:08,272
<i>(Bill) Rocky comes back out. He's like
a bull in a china closet. He really wants it.</i>

515
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:10,914
Apollo, left to the head.

516
00:47:11,040 --> 00:47:15,318
<i>(Stu) Now the champion's comin' back.
He's comin' off the floor now.</i>

517
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:21,678
<i>(Bill) Another left, another right.
Combinations into the face. That's Apollo!</i>

518
00:47:24,640 --> 00:47:27,916
Now the champ is taunting Rocky
to come and get some more.

519
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:29,951
Left. Another.

520
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:32,116
Another left!

521
00:47:33,080 --> 00:47:35,435
And Rocky's coming back now!

522
00:47:36,200 --> 00:47:38,953
Left! Right! Rocky's got him on the rope!

523
00:47:39,720 --> 00:47:41,870
OK, let's break it.

524
00:47:46,160 --> 00:47:49,709
There's no way they expected
this kind of hitting power.

525
00:47:49,840 --> 00:47:54,038
But the ability of the champion,
Apollo, is apparent.

526
00:47:56,080 --> 00:48:00,392
<i>(Stu) Apollo unloading,
Rocky really tight against the ropes.</i>

527
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:02,476
<i>(bell)</i>

528
00:48:07,040 --> 00:48:11,477
They're leading him back over to his
corner. Rocky can hardly find his way.

529
00:48:11,600 --> 00:48:14,558
- I told ya! I told ya!
- Your nose is broke.

530
00:48:14,680 --> 00:48:16,875
- How does it look?
- It's an improvement.

531
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:20,151
I want you to quit chuckin' and jivin'.
Stick and move.

532
00:48:20,280 --> 00:48:21,793
Go for the ribs.

533
00:48:21,920 --> 00:48:25,435
- Don't let that bastard breathe.
- The guy's great.

534
00:48:25,560 --> 00:48:29,030
He doesn't know it's a damn show.
He thinks it's a damn fight.

535
00:48:29,160 --> 00:48:31,913
- Finish this bum and let's go home.
- Right.

536
00:48:32,480 --> 00:48:34,630
Stay to the body! To his right!

537
00:48:34,760 --> 00:48:38,116
<i>(Stu) Here we go. Round two.
Creed predicted he would win in three.</i>

538
00:48:38,240 --> 00:48:41,710
Creed got knocked down in the first.
He came back at the end.

539
00:48:41,840 --> 00:48:43,831
<i>(Bill) Oh, he's working now.</i>

540
00:48:43,960 --> 00:48:46,349
Oh, that sharp left! Again, a hard right.

541
00:48:46,480 --> 00:48:48,914
He's working Rocky into the corner again.

542
00:48:49,040 --> 00:48:50,996
He's got Rocky back in the corner.

543
00:48:51,120 --> 00:48:55,477
Pelting him left and right.
He's bouncing up against the ring.

544
00:48:56,040 --> 00:48:58,873
<i>(Stu) Oh, Balboa's taking
a tremendous beating here.</i>

545
00:48:59,000 --> 00:49:03,516
<i>- (Bill) Battering him like a punching bag.
- (Stu) What's keeping him up?</i>

546
00:49:10,400 --> 00:49:12,834
<i>- He says he wants more!
- (Bill) He wants more!</i>

547
00:49:12,960 --> 00:49:17,317
You folks in front of your television
are watching a battle, I tell you that!

548
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:24,675
<i>(Stu) Balboa trying to fight back...
Ooh, a tremendous hook!</i>

549
00:49:24,800 --> 00:49:28,076
<i>(Bill) The champion is trying
to get himself out, but he can't.</i>

550
00:49:28,200 --> 00:49:31,556
He is being barraged
with lefts and rights to his body!

551
00:49:31,680 --> 00:49:35,150
<i>(Stu) Balboa is smacking the champion
right on the kisser!</i>

552
00:49:35,280 --> 00:49:37,510
<i>- (bell)
- The referee's stepped in.</i>

553
00:49:37,640 --> 00:49:39,870
They're ready to keep going!

554
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:42,116
Back to your corner!

555
00:49:42,240 --> 00:49:44,515
Come on, Creed!

556
00:49:44,880 --> 00:49:46,950
<i>(Stu) This is gonna be a tough one.</i>

557
00:50:50,840 --> 00:50:52,796
<i>(Bill) Hard left and right combination!</i>

558
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:55,878
<i>(Stu) What is keeping him up, Bill?
I don't know!</i>

559
00:50:58,080 --> 00:51:01,436
He can't even get his gloves up
to protect himself!

560
00:51:07,840 --> 00:51:09,876
Down! Down! Stay down!

561
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:13,151
<i>(Bill) Apollo dancing around
with his arms in the air!</i>

562
00:51:22,680 --> 00:51:24,875
Five!

563
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:27,355
Six! Seven!

564
00:51:28,040 --> 00:51:30,110
Eight! Nine!

565
00:51:35,160 --> 00:51:37,515
OK, OK. Come on!

566
00:51:39,560 --> 00:51:42,154
<i>(Bill) Apollo can't believe it!</i>

567
00:51:54,480 --> 00:51:56,436
<i>(bell)</i>

568
00:51:57,120 --> 00:52:00,908
<i>(Stu) The champion got a left to the ribs,
his right ribs.</i>

569
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:11,353
- You OK, champ?
- Yeah, I'm OK, I'm OK.

570
00:52:13,680 --> 00:52:16,956
I can't see nothin'.
I gotta open my eye. Cut me, Mick.

571
00:52:17,080 --> 00:52:20,436
- You don't wanna do it.
- Go on, cut me. Cut me.

572
00:52:27,560 --> 00:52:33,192
- You're bleeding inside. I'm gonna stop it.
- You ain't stoppin' nothin', man.

573
00:52:33,640 --> 00:52:35,995
You stop this fight, I'll kill ya.

574
00:52:42,160 --> 00:52:44,116
<i>(crowd chants) Rocky!</i>

575
00:52:49,920 --> 00:52:51,512
<i>(Bill) The 15th and final round.</i>

576
00:52:52,680 --> 00:52:56,958
<i>(crowd chants) Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

577
00:53:00,200 --> 00:53:03,158
<i>(Stu) They look like they've
been in a war, these two.</i>

578
00:53:11,320 --> 00:53:13,595
<i>(Bill) The champion really tightening!</i>

579
00:53:13,720 --> 00:53:17,474
And Apollo clearly protecting
his right side, his ribs.

580
00:53:22,400 --> 00:53:25,312
<i>(Stu) Hard left and right!
Look at the blood coming out!</i>

581
00:53:25,440 --> 00:53:28,671
<i>(Bill) Oh, he's spitting out blood now.</i>

582
00:53:30,720 --> 00:53:33,393
A tremendous right hand from Rocky!

583
00:53:33,520 --> 00:53:35,317
Go for it, Rock!

584
00:53:35,440 --> 00:53:38,193
<i>- (Bill) Listen to this crowd!
- (Stu) Left to the ribs.</i>

585
00:53:40,520 --> 00:53:44,195
Right to the chin!
He's got him up against the rope!

586
00:53:44,920 --> 00:53:46,319
<i>(bell)</i>

587
00:53:48,600 --> 00:53:51,797
<i>(Apollo) There ain't gonna be no rematch!</i>

588
00:53:51,920 --> 00:53:53,399
<i>(Rocky) Don't want one.</i>

589
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:05,629
Rocky, you went the distance, 15 rounds.

590
00:54:05,760 --> 00:54:08,797
- How do you feel?
- All right. It's all right.

591
00:54:08,920 --> 00:54:12,754
- Adrian! Adrian!
- What did you think in the 15th round...

592
00:54:12,880 --> 00:54:16,555
<i>- Rocky! Rocky!
- (MC) Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

593
00:54:16,680 --> 00:54:19,752
...your attention, please!
- Rocky! Rocky!

594
00:54:19,880 --> 00:54:24,351
Tonight we have had
the privilege of witnessing...

595
00:54:24,480 --> 00:54:30,032
...the greatest exhibition of guts
and stamina in the history of the ring!

596
00:54:30,160 --> 00:54:32,515
Adrian!

597
00:54:32,880 --> 00:54:34,632
Rocky!

598
00:54:34,760 --> 00:54:38,912
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have a split decision!

599
00:54:40,480 --> 00:54:43,756
- The judges voted...
- Adrian!

600
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:46,314
- Rocky!
...8- 7 for Creed!

601
00:54:49,240 --> 00:54:50,958
Your fans want a rematch.

602
00:54:51,080 --> 00:54:53,036
- There ain't gonna be one!
- Why not?

603
00:54:53,160 --> 00:54:57,073
- Come on! I had enough. Adrian!
- You heard him.

604
00:54:57,200 --> 00:55:00,556
- Let go! That's my friend. Rocco!
- He's everybody's friend.

605
00:55:00,680 --> 00:55:02,989
- You're breakin' my jacket!
- Let's go.

606
00:55:03,120 --> 00:55:06,192
- Paulie!
- Adrian! Adrian!

607
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:07,673
- Rocky!
- Adrian!

608
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:10,439
- Hey, where's your hat?
- I love you!

609
00:55:11,040 --> 00:55:13,270
<i>I love you.</i>

610
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:16,597
I love you! I love you!

611
00:55:17,720 --> 00:55:19,676
I love you!

612
00:57:21,240 --> 00:57:23,800
Visiontext subtitles: David Van-Cauter

